1️⃣ Remove duplicate compareGuesses

You currently have two compareGuesses functions. Keep only the updated version that uses getAbsoluteDistance() and validates the user input. Remove the earlier one.

2️⃣ Update updateScore logic

Right now updateScore returns the incremented value, but usually in a game you just want to update the global score:

function updateScore(winner) {
  if (winner === 'human') {
    humanScore++;
  } else if (winner === 'computer') {
    computerScore++;
  }
}


No need to return anything unless you specifically want the new score.

3️⃣ Example of using the game functions

Here’s a small snippet to simulate a round:

const humanGuess = 4;
const computerGuess = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10);
const target = generateTarget();

console.log("Target:", target);
console.log("Human guess:", humanGuess);
console.log("Computer guess:", computerGuess);

if (compareGuesses(humanGuess, computerGuess, target)) {
  console.log("Human wins this round!");
  updateScore('human');
} else {
  console.log("Computer wins this round!");
  updateScore('computer');
}

advanceRound();

console.log("Scores -> Human:", humanScore, "Computer:", computerScore);
console.log("Round number:", currentRoundNumber);
